.TH "sbi_remote_hfence_vvma" 9 "sbi_remote_hfence_vvma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sbi_remote_hfence_vvma \- Execute HFENCE.VVMA instructions on given remote harts for the current guest virtual address range.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sbi_remote_hfence_vvma
.BI "(const unsigned long *hart_mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned long start "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hart_mask" 12
A cpu mask containing all the target harts.
.IP "start" 12
Start of the current guest virtual address
.IP "size" 12
Total size of the current guest virtual address range.
.SH "RETURN"
None
